<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">The function of the</b> <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">IOBOARD_BE PBA </compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 21PBA01 </compcodenr></comp></title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-34C6A3E5-E809-4139-80CC-275A8CCF9EDC"><p class="- topic/p ">What is the function of the <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">IOBOARD_BE PBA </compname><compcodenr class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr " translate="no"> 21PBA01 </compcodenr></comp>? 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Functional description</category></metadata></prolog><conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody "><section id="GUID-F5034822-753A-4C8B-A7CD-E44CE7EBD702" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Functional description</title><p class="- topic/p "> The IOBOARD_BE PBA (Basic Engine) is a power driver board which controls the sensor/actuators for the following functions: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Media handling 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">External output (only EXO_WIND_CLAMP_MO, EXO_WIND_FLAP_MO, EXO_WIND_DRV_MO) 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Cleaning and Maintenance 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Y motion system (only YMS_CAR_MO, YMS_CAR_MO_FAN) 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Curing 
</p></li></ul><p class="- topic/p "> Two remote bus interfaces are implemented, X550 upstream connected to µmorpf, X551 downstream to INK_SUPPLY. 
</p><note id="GUID-5C5D9BC7-31C7-468F-A77A-91AE352E1EF0" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">The 2 connectors (RJ45) are identical. Please note the correct position of the colored bundles. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> The board has dedicated power supply inputs for the various functions. These can be continuous available or interlocked (controlled by DISTRIBUTION). 
</p></note></section><section id="GUID-89A97054-E88E-4AB0-94C1-3A88000CB399" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Illustration</title><fig id="GUID-36CF4AE7-2ADF-43B6-BF39-FE68EA31EBAA" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-C15D6A84-A335-4497-9187-90ED3D2C5DAF-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-C15D6A84-A335-4497-9187-90ED3D2C5DAF-svg.svg"/></fig><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Main connections on PBA:</b> 
